(216, 'dyannlabo', 'dylabo@icloud.com', 'Rev123!', 'WJ8Lcp2WvncJTq6lARUgNgtCAxI98J', null, '2022-03-11 11:11:15', 0, null, null, '2022-08-11 11:58:20', '98.38.129.30', null, '0:1:45:4:1:0~4:1:45:3:20:0~0:1:45:3:20:0~5:1:45:3:19:0~5:1:45:3:20:0~4:1:48:3:7:0~0:1:48:3:7:0~3:2:1:1:abraham:0~4:1:42:16:22:0~0:1:42:16:22:0~3:2:1:1:abraham:0~4:0:1:20:17:0~0:0:1:20:17:0~3:2:1:1:abraham:0~0:0:1:20:11:0~4:0:1:20:11:0~0:0:1:18:-1:0~0:0:1:19:-1:0~0:0:1:20:10:0~3:2:1:1:abraham:0~0:0:19:33:-1:0~4:1:40:20:-1:0~4:1:40:19:1:0~0:0:19:33:-1:0~4:1:40:18:1:0~0:0:19:33:-1:0', null, null, '<p>Psalm 139:1 &ndash; Oh, Yahweh, you have searched me and you know me.</p> <p>You yourself know when I sit down and when I stand up. You discern what I think from afar.</p> <p>You measure out where I go and when I rest, yes, you are acquainted with all my road.</p> <p>For an utterance does not have to be on my tongue, behold, O Lord, you know it altogether.</p> <p>You have enclosed my back and my front and you laid your hand on me.</p> <p>Such knowledge is too wonderful for me. It is so high I am unable to attain it.</p> <p>What does it say?</p> <p>It is saying that God has searched me and knows me. When I sit and stand, where I go and when I rest, utterance on my tongue he knows it. He has enclosed me from back to front and laid his hand on me. This knowledge is so wonderful and so high I cannot attain it.</p> <p>What is it saying to me?</p> <p>God knows me better than I know myself. He has searched me and knows me. To the point of when I sit or stand, rest or go, and what I am thinking or going to say. He has enclosed me and laid his hand on me. I am protected and not alone. The knowledge is so wonderful and so high that I cannot grasp it.</p> <p>Short prayer:</p> <p>Thank you so much, Father, for my life and that I am not alone, for it is you who has searched me and know me, when I sit or stand, when I rest or go, and for an utterance does not have to be on my tongue and you know it altogether. Thank you, God, that you have enclosed me and laid your hand on me. What protection, Father, that you have given me. This knowledge is too wonderful and high for me to grasp it, Father. I thank you that today I will have this knowledge in my thoughts and walk forth pleasing you, Father.</p> <p>June 27, 2022</p> <p>Psalm 139:7-10 &ndash; Where could I go from your spirit? Where could I flee from your presence? If I ascend up into heaven you are there. If I make my bed in Sheol, behold, you are there! If I take the wings of the morning dawn, if I settle in the fartherst part of the sea, even there your hand will lead me and your right hand will hold me.</p> <p>What does it say?</p> <p>No matter where I am at or where I go, God will always be there to lead me and hold me.</p> <p>What is it saying to me?</p> <p>There are times when I feel alone and lost, but no matter where I am or what situation I am in, God is there to lead me and hold me.</p> <p>Short prayer:</p> <p>Thank you, God, that I can enjoy life and enjoy everything that you have created; that no matter where I am, physically or mentally, you are there to lead me and hold me.</p> <p>July 5, 2022</p> <p>Matthew 11:28-30</p> <p>Come to me, all you who are laboring and have been loaded down with burdens, and I will give you rest.</p> <p>Take my yoke upon you and learn from me, because I am meek and humble in heart, and you will find rest for your souls.</p> <p>For my yoke is kind and my burden is light.</p> <p>What does it say?</p> <p>Jesus yoke is kind (system of grace and love) &ndash; he will give me rest from my burdens and rest for my soul. His burden is light. He is meek and humble.</p> <p>What is it saying to me?</p> <p>When I feel burdened down, go to Jesus, who is full of grace and love, a yoke that is kind, and he will give me rest for my soul.</p> <p>Short prayer:</p> <p>Thank you, Jesus, that I walk today with grace and love and that you give rest to my soul.</p> <p>July 6, 2022</p> <p>Mathew 12:36</p> <p>And I say to you, that every careless word that people speak, they will give account of it on the Day of Judgment.</p> <p>What does it say?</p> <p>Careless words that people speak will give account on Day of Judgment.</p> <p>What is it saying to me?</p> <p>What would God think of the words I say? Think about what God desires before words come out of my mouth. Make sure they are not careless, but thought out and a blessing to people.</p> <p>Short prayer:</p> <p>Thank you, God, for helping me have your heart and what comes out of my mouth is thoughtful and wanting to do your will, no matter what my emotions are. Thank you, God, that I obey you and your word!</p> <p>Matt 13:16-17</p> <p>But blessed are your eyes, for they see, and your ears, for they hear. For truly I say to you, that many prophets and righteous people desired to see the things that you see, and did not see them, and to hear the things that you hear, and did not hear them.</p> <p>What does it say?</p> <p>You are blessed because your eyes see and your ears hear the things that the prophets and righteous people desired to hear and see.</p> <p>What is it saying to me?</p> <p>Jesus spoke in parables so that the people who desired the truth would take the time to understand as opposed to arrogant people who would not give his lessons the time of day. To read the word and find out what God wants for your life takes effort, but is rewarded with understanding and enlightenment, revealing great secrets that prophets and righteous people desired to know.</p> <p>Short prayer:</p> <p>Thank you, God, that my eyes continue to see and my ears continue to hear your great truths and that I am the seed who fell on the good soil and yielded much fruit; that I continue to grow in your word and not let the things of this world get in the way of what is really important, which is doing your will.</p> <p>July 8, 2022</p> <p>Matt 14:13</p> <p>Now when Jesus heard it, he withdrew from there in a boat by himself to a solitary place.</p> <p>What does it say?</p> <p>Jesus found a solitary place.</p> <p>What is it saying to me?</p> <p>Sometimes it is good to be alone to take care of your own needs.</p> <p>Short prayer:</p> <p>Thank you, God, that I can listen to my body and find time to be alone with you and talk to you; that I can learn to say no to things when it would be better to take care of myself.</p> <p>July 10, 2022</p> <p>But the things that come out of the mouth come from the heart and they defile the person.</p> <p>What is it saying?</p> <p>The heart, which is the source of life, will be made known from the mouth, and the things that come out of it can defile a person, not whether or not their hands are washed before eating bread.</p> <p>What is it saying to me?</p> <p>Keep my heart pure by reading the word of God and praying and speaking with God so that my heart stays pure and the things I say will be a blessing to people.</p> <p>Short prayer:</p> <p>God, thank you that my heart stays pure and out of my mouth flows blessings and magnifies you!</p>'),
