my words, and the years of your life will be many.</p> <p><strong>Proverbs 1:20-21</strong></p> <p>20--Lady Wisdom shouts aloud in the street, in public places she raises her voice.<br /> 21--At the head of noisy streets she calls out, where the city gates open she speaks her words,</p> <p><strong>I Kings 12:4-11</strong></p> <p>4--&ldquo;Your father made our yoke hard, but now lighten the hard service of your father and his heavy yoke that he put on us, and we will serve you.&rdquo;<br /> 5--And he said to them, &ldquo;Depart for three days, then come back to me.&rdquo; So the people departed.</p> <p>6--Then King Rehoboam sought advice from the old men who had stood before Solomon his father while he was still alive, saying, &ldquo;How do you advise me to answer this people?&rdquo;<br /> 7--They spoke to him, saying, &ldquo;If today you will be a servant to this people and will serve them, then answer them and speak good words to them, and they will always be your servants.&rdquo;<br /> 8--But he rejected the advice that the old men had given him, and he asked the advice of the young men who had grown up with him and who stood before him.<br /> 9--He said to them, &ldquo;How do you advise that we should answer this people who have spoken to me, saying, &lsquo;Lighten the yoke that your father put on us&rsquo;?&rdquo;</p> <p>10--The young men who had grown up with him spoke to him, saying, &ldquo;This is what you should tell this people who spoke to you, saying, &lsquo;Your father made our yoke heavy, but lighten it for us.&rsquo;&rdquo; You should say to them, &lsquo;My little thing is thicker than my father&rsquo;s waist.<br /> 11--And now, although my father loaded a heavy yoke upon you, I will add to your yoke; my father disciplined you with whips, but I will discipline you with scorpions.&rsquo;&rdquo;</p> <p>Ten tribes split away and basically never return&hellip;</p> <p><strong>II CHR 22:10-12</strong></p> <p>10--Now when Athaliah the mother of Ahaziah saw that her son was dead, she rose up and eliminated all the royal seed of the house of Judah.<br /> 11--But Jehoshabeath, the daughter of the king, took Joash the son of Ahaziah and stole him away from among the king&rsquo;s sons who were being put to death, and put him and his nurse in a bedroom. So Jehoshabeath, the daughter of king Jehoram, the wife of Jehoiada the priest (for she was the sister of Ahaziah), hid him from Athaliah so that she did not kill him.<br /> 12--He was with them, hiding in the house of God for six years, while Athaliah reigned over the land.</p> <p><strong>II CHR 24:2-4</strong></p> <p>2Joash did what was right in the eyes of Yahweh all the days of Jehoiada the priest,<br /> 3and Jehoiada acquired two wives for himb and he fathered sons and daughters.<br /> 4Some time later, Joash determined to restore the house of Yahweh.</p> <p><strong>II CHR 24:15-22</strong></p> <p>15--But Jehoiada grew old and was full of days, and he died. He was 130 years old when he died.<br /> 16--They buried him in the city of David among the kings, because he had done good in Israel and toward God and his house.<br /> 17--Now after the death of Jehoiada, the officials of Judah came and bowed down to the king. And the king listened to them.<br /> 18--They abandoned the house of Yahweh the God of their fathers and served the Asherah poles and the idols, and wrath came on Judah and Jerusalem for this guilt of theirs.<br /> 19--Yet he sent prophets to them to bring them back to Yahweh, and they testified against them but they would not listen.<br /> 20--And the spirit of God clothed Zechariah the son of Jehoiada the priest, and he stood above the people and said to them, &ldquo;This is what God says: &lsquo;Why do you disobey the commandments of Yahweh? You will not be prosperous! Because you have forsaken Yahweh, he has also forsaken you.&rsquo;&rdquo;<br /> 21--They conspired against him and stoned him with stones at the commandment of the king in the court of the house of Yahweh.<br /> 22--So Joash the king did not remember the kindness that Jehoiada his father had done to him, but killed his son. When he died, he said, &ldquo;May Yahweh see this and repay it.&rdquo;</p> <p>So, two aspects:</p> <p>1 &ndash; To whom am I listening?</p> <p>A &ndash; Compromised Medical system</p> <p>B &ndash; Compromised media.</p> <p>2 &ndash; How can I help to whom others are listening?</p> <p><strong>Hebrews 3:12,13</strong></p> <p>12--See to it, brothers and sisters, lest there will be in any one of you an evil, unbelieving heart leading you to fall away from the living God.<br /> &nbsp;13--But exhort one another every day, so long as it is still called &ldquo;today,&rdquo; lest any one of you is hardened by the deceitfulness of sin.</p> <p><strong>II Timothy 3:13-17</strong></p> <p>13--but evil people and impostors will go from bad to worse, deceiving and being deceived.<br /> 14--But you&mdash;continue in the things that you have learned and firmly believed, because you know who you learned them from,<br /> 15--and also that from a baby you have known the sacred writings, which are able to give you wisdom leading to salvation through trust in Christ Jesus.<strong>-- Timothy learned from Paul, good choice!</strong></p> <p>16--All Scripture is God-breathed and is profitable for teaching, for reproof, for correction, for training in righteousness,<br /> 17--so that the person dedicated to God can be fully capable, thoroughly equipped for every good work.</p> <p><strong>II Timothy 4:1-5</strong></p> <p>1--I solemnly charge you in the presence of God and Christa Jesus, who is going to judge the living and the dead, and by his appearing and his kingdom:<br /> 2--preach the word; be ready at convenient times and at inconvenient times; reprove, rebuke, and exhort with all patience and teaching.<br /> 3--For the time will come when they will not tolerate sound doctrine; but having itching ears, they will pile up teachers for themselves, to suit their own desires,<br /> 4--and will turn away from listening to the truth and turn aside to myths.<br /> 5--But you, be clearheaded in all circumstances, endure suffering, do the work of an evangelist, fully carry out your ministry.</p> <p><strong>Ephesians 4:11-16</strong></p> <p>11--And he gave some to be apostles, and some to be prophets, and some to be evangelists, and some to be pastors and teachers,<br /> 12--for the equipping of the holy ones for the work of ministry, with the goal of building up the body of Christ,<br /> 13--until we all attain to the unity of the faithd and of the knowledge of the Son of God, growing into a mature person, attaining to the measure of the full stature of Christ,<br /> 14--so that we are no longer children, tossed here and there and blown about with every wind of doctrine, by people&rsquo;s trickery and craftiness in deceitful scheming.<br /> 15--But speaking the truth in love, we are to grow up in every way into him who is the head, Christ,<br /> 16--from whom the whole body, being fitted together and held together by every supporting ligament, with each individual part doing its proper function,e produces the growth of the body with the goal of building itself up in love.</p>'),
